message: Undid revision 922479313 by [[Special:Contributions/Megyeye|Megyeye]] ([[User talk:Megyeye|talk]]) With respect, I don't think this rewrite has clarified the law. E.g. it says that only member states party to the 1968 Convention must recognise the EU identifier, but the Convention is not referred to in the operative provisions of 2411/98. Article 3 binds any member state that requires the display of a distinguishing sign - not just Convention signatories. Some tweaks to original text suggested.
